<paragraph blockId="109.[151,1437,152,410]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,449,152,178]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
This species is based on a single specimen. This is very similar to specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="braunii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">G. braunii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in fact it was identified as such by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stauffer, F." box="[723,898,190,216]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Venezuelica" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 10" part="20" refId="ref124409" refString="Stauffer, F. (1997) Estudio morfologico y taxonomico de Geonoma spinescens H. Wendl. ex Burret (Arecaceae) y descripcion de una nueva variedad. Acta Botanica Venezuelica 20: 1 - 10." title="Estudio morfologico y taxonomico de Geonoma spinescens H. Wendl. ex Burret (Arecaceae) y descripcion de una nueva variedad" type="journal article" year="1997">Stauffer (1997</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stauffer" authorityYear="1997" box="[944,1251,190,217]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="spinescens" variety="braunii">
<emphasis box="[944,1100,190,217]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">G. spinescens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1164,1251,190,216]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">braunii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, the fruits of the specimen (in a separate packet, see Appendix IV, Plate 52) have an operculum, and because of this the specimen is here recognized as a separate species. It is the only species outside of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wendland ex Spruce" authorityYear="1871" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congesta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Geonoma congesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade to have fruits with an operculum. Apart from the operculum, the specimen bears no resemblance to species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wendland ex Spruce" authorityYear="1871" box="[500,636,345,371]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congesta">
<emphasis box="[500,636,345,371]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">G. congesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade but appears similar to specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1134,1252,345,371]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="braunii">
<emphasis box="[1134,1252,345,371]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">G. braunii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="109.[151,1437,152,410]" box="[198,1297,384,410]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,500,384,410]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
